<TITLE> Tk 38mln for journo training </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 10 (bdnews24.com)  The next fiscal's budget has allocated Tk 38 million for training journalists. The allocation will be spent through the state-owned Press Institute of Bangladesh, finance minister AMA Muhith said in his budget speech Thursday. "I would ask the senior and well-known journalists from newspapers, media and other institutes to organise workshops for journalists," he said. Muhith also asked senior journalists and editors to be positive in developing quality and professionalism in journalism. Moreover, the minister called on newspaper owners to give salaries and wages in line with the wage board. b
